wikipedia_page.main: Thomas John Wynn, 2nd Baron Newborough (3 April 1802 – 15 November 1832), was a British peer.

response: On 15 November 1832, on the death of his older brother, Thomas Wynn, 2nd Baron Newborough, he succeeded to the titles of 3rd Baron Newborough of Bodvean, and 5th Baronet Wynn of Boduan.
* Thomas Wynn, 2nd Baron Newborough (1802–1832), British peer
